  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Currently when kubelet is running in a container writing secretes doesn't work. The problematic workflow is:\n1. Kubelet mounts `tmpfs` as a secret volume using `nsenter_mounter` in host's namespace\n2. Kubelet reads secretes from API server\n3. Kubelet tries to write secretes to the newly created volume, but as it resides in host's namespace it fails.\n\nThis will be solved with https://github.com/docker/docker/pull/15648, but before it happens we will need some temporary solution. One workaround is to use `nsenter` to write data similarly to how we have mounted it.\n\nThis is a blocker to run kubelet and other k8s components as docker containers, which should greatly simplify UX for new setups.\n\n@dchen1107 @smarterclayton @brendandburns \n",
